node.text:
BStrong and Global Empowerment teams have mobilized a thorough, detailed effort to aid this crisis after the tragic 7.2 earthquake that has destroyed the southern coast of Haiti. 

We have secured 1.4 million in medical supplies, food and aid to be distributed in the coming weeks. We are currently on the ground assessing and beginning to procure and distribute aid we have secured from the north. We will be flying in with local military and green berets continuing to access the situation for research and recovery. 

1700 deaths have been reported, but the numbers are climbing and look to be in the thousands, with more than 5k persons injured, and counting. 

Thousands are homeless and desperate as buildings are unsafe, condemned or crumbled. The initial areas we will be distributing aid are Les Cayes, Jeremie and La Petite Anse.

Our team has traveled to Haiti more than 90 times providing aid & rebuilding since the tragic 2010 earthquake. We are very experienced and prepared for this, particularly in this area, which is critical since relief work is riddled with corruption, waste and error. This is precisely what we do.

We will be working on rescue, recovery and rebuild throughout September as this is a long and arduous process for these poor people who have endured the unimaginable twice.

As always, 100% goes to the effort. We will keep you posted on addition updates. Please donate with the link in my bio. www.bethenny.com/bstrong #thisisacrisis #prayforhaiti @globalempowermentmission @foxandfriends @foxnews #haiti

node.text:
The truth is most people don’t work that hard 🤷🏻‍♀️

I was a natural food chef, I had a business called Bethenny Bakes and another one called Princess Pashmina, all while I was broke. I was constantly thinking about ways to be successful and how to execute on my ideas. If you are a true entrepreneur, it’s very challenging to turn it off.

I share a lot of my business tips on my @justbwithbethenny podcast. 🎙I also talk to people who started from the bottom and now they are at the top. Who would you like to see me interview next? 🎧

Smart Salads with Bethenny 🥗

Here are my favorite tips for creating a salad ⬇️

1. Avoid already chopped greens because they perish and brown quickly. 🥬
2. Find a firm, but not hard, avocado (not as soft as my tush).🥑
3. Buy small grape tomatoes that will keep longer in your fridge. (People don’t refrigerate tomatoes to preserve flavor but I do).🍅
4. Use pre boiled bagged eggs. I use the whole egg. 🥚
5. Salt and pepper your greens before dressing them with @skinnygirlbrand.🧂

You may have seen this clip on my show @thebigshotonmax. We did the avocado tush test in the latest episode. What should I make next?

BStrong and Global Empowerment teams have mobilized a thorough, detailed effort to aid this crisis after the tragic 7.2 earthquake that has destroyed the southern coast of Haiti. 

We have secured 1.4 million in medical supplies, food and aid to be distributed in the coming weeks. We are currently on the ground assessing and beginning to procure and distribute aid we have secured from the north. We will be flying in with local military and green berets continuing to access the situation for research and recovery. 

1700 deaths have been reported, but the numbers are climbing and look to be in the thousands, with more than 5k persons injured, and counting. 

Thousands are homeless and desperate as buildings are unsafe, condemned or crumbled. The initial areas we will be distributing aid are Les Cayes, Jeremie and La Petite Anse.

Our team has traveled to Haiti more than 90 times providing aid & rebuilding since the tragic 2010 earthquake. We are very experienced and prepared for this, particularly in this area, which is critical since relief work is riddled with corruption, waste and error. This is precisely what we do.

We will be working on rescue, recovery and rebuild throughout September as this is a long and arduous process for these poor people who have endured the unimaginable twice.

As always, 100% goes to the effort. We will keep you posted on addition updates. Please donate with the link in my bio. www.bethenny.com/bstrong #thisisacrisis #prayforhaiti @globalempowermentmission @foxandfriends @foxnews #haiti

A major 7.2 magnitude earthquake has hit Haiti. Mass casualties are feared.

The devastating earthquake in Haiti in 2010 is what made me want to work on crisis relief. The pain & suffering in this poor country has been inexplicable. History is repeating itself after this community has struggled to rebuild.

We will be distributing aid in the affected regions which is the south coast. 

As always 💯 of your donation goes directly to the effort. This is a crisis and we are there to help.

Our teams are already on the ground and more support is on the way. Xo 😘 and thank you… 🇭🇹#prayforhaiti #donatenow 
@globalempowermentmission #Bstrong #HelpHaiti #linkinbio

If I were a “filterer” I would have gotten rid of my lines and my dark circles, but this is me at 50. #zeroglam #zerofilter

Why do I mention this all the time? Because I think it’s important for young women to know that being flawed is truthful and real, and that filtering yourself into someone fictitious is actually damaging to girls’ and women’s self esteem. It’s courageous and beautiful to be real at any age.

node.text:
The truth is most people don’t work that hard 🤷🏻‍♀️

I was a natural food chef, I had a business called Bethenny Bakes and another one called Princess Pashmina, all while I was broke. I was constantly thinking about ways to be successful and how to execute on my ideas. If you are a true entrepreneur, it’s very challenging to turn it off.

I share a lot of my business tips on my @justbwithbethenny podcast. 🎙I also talk to people who started from the bottom and now they are at the top. Who would you like to see me interview next? 🎧
